          • [ - ] Castle - member since 08-Sep-15

            In this match we will see, in my opinion, two best managers of the last season facing each other. West Ham was the most overachieving team after Leicester, and without Payet's and Lanzini's injuries they would have been challenging for the title or at least finished in top 4. This season, however, neither have got best out of their teams which often happens after one good season as it's simply hard to reach the same level. I still see both teams doing better in the second half of the season. West Ham have shown some encouraging signs and decision not to sack Bilic will definitely pay off for them! In this match I believe West Ham have an advantage. Their form looks to be turning and in Ayew has finally getting a chance to prove himself. 1-2 for Hammers, although Leicester could fight a draw as well.
